<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: POWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Skeletal remains believed to be those of a man were retrieved from Sycamore 
Canyon County Park in Poway, authorities said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies located scattered human bones about 6 p.m. Tuesday in 
brush-covered terrain south of Poway Road and west of Sycamore Park Drive, Sgt. 
Manny Castillo said, adding that clothes and personal belongings were found 
near the remains. 
</P>
<P>
Castillo said the remains were discovered Sunday by a motorcyclist who did not 
report the finding until Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The coroner is attempting to identify the remains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
