<P>
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Cutting Congress' Budget 
</P>
<P>
By a vote of 167 to 246, the House rejected an amendment cutting nearly all 
areas of the 1990 legislative branch budget (above) by 6.25%, for a savings of 
$97 million. "What used to be called the '$1-billion Congress' has become the 
'$2-billion Congress,' " said amendment spon sor Bill Frenzel (R-Minn.) 
Opponent Jerry Lewis (R-Redlands) said the amendment "would cut some items that 
are very fundamental in terms of the members' ability to work around this 
place." 
</P>
<P>
Members voting yes supported a 6.25% cut in the fiscal 1990 legislative branch 
budget. 
</P>
