<HEADLINE>
<P>
GROWTH HORMONE IN MILK SUPPLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I had read some time ago that new genetic growth hormones were being introduced 
to promote milk production and I wondered what the need was for increased 
production when, for years, we have subsidized the dairy industry. 
</P>
<P>
Epstein's article gives us the answer -- $500 million in annual worldwide sales 
by five chemical manufacturers -- and the FDA is ready to approve it! What 
about the health and growth of infants and children, the threat of cancer and 
other consumer health risks? 
</P>
<P>
It really burns me up that medications, tested, tried, approved and 
successfully used in Europe, are being held back in the United States by the 
FDA that is about to allow a potentially dangerous drug into our food chain. 
</P>
<P>
SHIRLEY WOLF 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica 
</P>
</TEXT>
