recalcitrant sheep for loading. Arthur Corona was philosophical in defeat, 
although he faces a $1,000 fine and a maximum six-month jail sentence after 
being found guilty on a misdemeanor charge. "If it's God's will for my life 
that I don't have the sheep in San Pedro, so be it," he said. TODD ROSENBERG 
/Los Angeles Times 
