<P>
ABORTION ISSUE AT THE FAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
While my wife and I had a very pleasant time at the recent San Fernando Valley 
Fair, it was somewhat marred by the presence of an anti-abortion exhibit. 
</P>
<P>
The fact that I disagree with their point of view is not the issue. The fair is 
supposed to be an agricultural exhibition, not a political or religious event. 
Considering the turmoil surrounding the abortion issue, someone at the fair's 
booking office obviously decided to make a statement. 
</P>
<P>
I'm making a statement too. We will not attend the fair in the future if this 
continues. Or maybe we'll bring a vocal contingent of pro-choice people with us 
and raise the barn roof. 
</P>
<P>
HOWARD LEVINE 
