<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOYOUSEEWHATISEE WINS AT DEL MAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DEL MAR 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Doyouseewhatisee led wire to wire, beating favored Green Baby by three lengths 
in the $82,050 De Anza Stakes for 2-year-olds Wednesday at Del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
Doyouseewhatisee, ridden by Martin Pedroza, covered the six furlongs in 1:09 
2/5 for his second straight victory. The fourth betting choice of the crowd of 
14,382 returned $13.60, $5.40 and $4.20. 
</P>
<P>
Green Baby, the 8-5 favorite, paid $3.20 and $3.20, and Drag Race returned 
$6.80. 
</P>
