<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LYNWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
WELL CLEANUP STUDY OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has approved hiring a Pasadena engineering firm to study how 
to remove excessive iron and manganese from a municipal water well. 
</P>
<P>
James M. Montgomery Engineers Inc. has been awarded a $20,000 contract to 
figure out how to treat the well, which the city built last year but never 
operated because the chemicals exceeded state health limits. 
</P>
<P>
The study will also determine how much it will cost to remove the contaminants, 
Public Works Director Joseph Y. Wang said. 
</P>
<P>
Six other wells provide more than enough water for the city, Wang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
