<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GANG UNIT ARRESTS MURDER SUSPECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A suspected gang member has been arrested by Los Angeles police for allegedly 
gunning down a West Los Angeles man in Pacific Palisades early July 29. 
</P>
<P>
Members of the Los Angeles Police Department's anti-gang unit, Community 
Resources Against Street Hoodlums, arrested Ruben Rodriguez, 24, shortly after 
5 a.m. at a relative's apartment in Mar Vista Gardens, Detective Bill Humphry 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Humphry said Efigenio Vital, 20, was shot and killed on Asilomar Boulevard in 
the seaside community after an argument with Rodriguez and other gang members 
at a party July 29. Police say Vital was an associate of a rival gang. 
</P>
<P>
Vital and several friends apparently drove to a cul-de-sac at the end of 
Asilomar Boulevard above Pacific Coast Highway to enjoy the ocean view after 
the party and another car carrying Rodriguez arrived later. The occupants 
called out the name of a gang, then fired several shots, fatally wounding 
Vital, Humphry said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
