<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FIREFIGHTERS CITED FOR HALTING SUICIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles Fire Capt. Donald Stukey and Firefighter Jeffrey Dapper have been 
awarded departmental commendations for rescuing a man who was threatening to 
commit suicide last October. 
</P>
<P>
Stukey and Dapper found the man -- incoherent and semiconscious -- at Florence 
Avenue and Main Street atop a 50-foot power pole, trapped between high-voltage 
wires, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The firefighters carefully positioned their ladder and removed the man from the 
pole, saving his life, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Stukey's and Dapper's "performance under dangerous conditions showed 
initiative, responsibility and a deep respect for life," departmental reports 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
