<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
U.S. Facilities Corp. posted net income of $605,000 for the second quarter, 
contrasted with a loss of $194,000 for the like period last year. Revenue rose 
55% to $14.9 million from $9.6 million. For the six-month period, net income 
rose to $1 million, contrasted with a net loss of $499,000 for the first half 
of 1988. Revenue increased 58% to $29 million from $18.4 million. The Costa 
Mesa-based company attributed the improved results to higher reinsurance 
premiums from its insurance subsidiary, higher fees earned by its US Benefits 
Inc. subsidiary, and increased investment income. 
