</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mark C. Wessel has been appointed vice president of international sales for 
Parker Automotive Corp.'s CarbonClean products. He will be the Costa Mesa 
company's liaison with foreign distributors and will be responsible for the 
development of additional sales in other parts of the world. Previously, Wessel 
was general manager of Franz Amrhein &amp; Co., S.A., the distributor for John 
Deere farm and industrial equipment in Central America and for Honda Motor 
Corp. in Costa Rica. Before that, he was general manager and sales manager for 
Texas Instruments' Central American affiliate, Corporation Sigma S.A. in San 
Jose, Costa Rica. Parker's CarbonClean products are used to clean pollutants 
from internal combustion engines. 
