<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: WEST HOLLYWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
GARBAGE CONTRACT AWARDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has approved a five-year, $2.4-million contract with Waste 
Management of Sun Valley Inc. to provide residential garbage collection and 
recycling. 
</P>
<P>
The company will begin serving residential customers Sept. 1, with the city's 
new recycling program to begin on a limited basis early next year, public works 
Director Chuck Bergson said. 
</P>
<P>
The company will service single-family homes and apartment units where trash 
containers of 45 gallons or less are used, Bergson said. 
</P>
<P>
About 20 other waste disposal companies continue to contract with businesses 
and large apartment buildings for commercial pickups in West Hollywood. In 
July, however, those companies were required to have city licenses for the 
first time. 
</P>
<P>
For years, West Hollywood residents have complained about noisy garbage trucks 
in neighborhoods during prohibited hours and of streets strewn with garbage 
mishandled by carriers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
