WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
RULES ON SAVING WATER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has adopted permanent water conservation measures based on 
emergency regulations implemented during last summer's drought. 
</P>
<P>
Beginning Sept. 7, the city will ban the washing down of driveways and patios, 
the watering of lawns between 10 a.m. and 4 p.m., and the serving of water at 
restaurants unless requested by patrons. 
</P>
<P>
However, lawns may be watered daily rather than on alternate days, as was 
ordered last year. A ban on filling empty pools and spas has also been 
rescinded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
