<P>
AIRPORT MAY GET RESTAURANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city has cleared the way for a 180-seat restaurant at Santa Monica 
Airport's new Clover Field Terminal and Administration Building. 
</P>
<P>
The Council voted 6 to 0 Tuesday night to authorize lease negotiations with Los 
Angeles restaurateurs Brian and Michael Vidor to build a two-story, 
4,600-square-foot restaurant, bar and concession stand. 
</P>
<P>
The Vidor restaurant, "The Typhoon," would be open six days a week and offer 
moderately priced Chinese and American cuisine. The Vidors would hold a 15-year 
lease with an option for a 10-year extension, and pay the city an annual rent 
of $38,452 plus 4% and 6% royalty fees on food and beverage sales. 
</P>
<P>
The Vidors' other restaurants include a Mexican food chain and a French bistro 
in the Northwest. 
</P>
