<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENICE ARTS FESTIVAL IS SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The sixth annual Venice Summer Arts and Crafts Festival will be held Sunday, 
featuring more than 100 booths, music from bands such as "The Bone Daddys" and 
a children's game area. 
</P>
<P>
The festival, whose theme is, "Celebrate Venice -- a continuing tradition," 
will be held on West Washington Boulevard, which will be closed to traffic from 
Venice Boulevard to Westminster Avenue. The hours are 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
There will be park-and-ride lots at Broadway Elementary School, 1015 Lincoln 
Boulevard (at Broadway); Coeur D'Alene School, 810 Coeur D'Alene Ave., and 
Chiat-Day Advertising, 320 Hampton St.. The $3 parking fee will be donated to 
the festival. 
</P>
<P>
Profits from the event will be donated to the Oakwood Youth Recreational 
Programs and for tree-planting on West Washington Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
Entertainment will feature Musicians Against Crack. An autographed jersey from 
Los Angeles Raiders running back Marcus Allen will be auctioned off. Raider 
Hall-of-Famer Willie Brown will sign autographs and give away a four-day 
cruise. 
</P>
